Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Remove the @slow cooked British pork{425%grams} shoulder from the packaging. Place in an #ovenproof dish{} along with the juices and cover loosely with #foil{}. Set aside.

Chop the @potatoes{450%grams} lengthways into 1cm slices, then chop into 1cm wide chips (no need to peel).

Pop the chips onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with oil, sprinkle over the @roasted spice and herb blend{1%sachet}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat.

Spread out in a single layer. 

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, bake the pork on the middle shelf until piping hot and the chips on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%mins}. Turn the chips halfway through.

== Avocado Salsa ==

In the meantime, halve the @avocado{1} and remove the stone. Use a #tablespoon{} to scoop the flesh out onto a board. Cut into 1cm chunks and pop into a #medium bowl{}.

Cut the @medium tomato{1} into 1cm chunks and add to the avocado bowl. Drizzle over a little @olive oil{}.

Cut the @lime{1} into wedges, then squeeze some juice into the avo and tomato. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then set aside.

== Slaw ==

In another medium bowl, combine the @sugar{1/2%tsp} and @olive oil{1%tbsp}(for the dressing) with a good squeeze of lime juice.

Add the @coleslaw mix{120%grams}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss together. Set aside.

== Spiced Chips ==

Lay the @plain taco tortillas{4} onto another large baking tray in a single layer and rub each with a little @oil{}. Season with @salt{} and set aside.

Once the pork is cooked, remove from the oven. 

> IMPORTANT: Ensure the pork is piping hot throughout.

Pop the #tortilla baking tray{} onto the middle shelf and bake until golden and crispy, ~{4-6%minutes}.

> TIP: Tostada means 'toasted', so make sure they're crispy!

== Honey Harissa Pulled Pork ==

Meanwhile, reserve 1 tbsp of pork cooking juices per person, then discard the foil and any remaining cooking juices.

Use two #forks{} to shred the pork as finely as you can, then stir through the @harissa paste{50%grams}, reserved cooking juices and the @honey{1%tbsp}(for the dressing). Season with @salt{}, @pepper{} and the remaining lime juice.

== To Serve ==

When everything's ready, transfer the tostadas to your plates.

Top with the harissa pulled pork, then drizzle over the @Greek style natural yoghurt{75%grams}. Spoon the avo salsa on top.

Serve the slaw and chips alongside. Pop the @mayonnaise{2%tbsp}(for dipping) on the side for dipping.

> TIP: Tostadas are best enjoyed eaten by hand - get stuck in!